2f:"$Sreact.suspense"
3:T6e4,So whats the problem here? The problem is that now you can't stop even if you tried. You are at the whim of the entity. Imagine if you were in a
situation where your mother would be killed if you smoked a cigarette. The entity appears with the delightful thought, but now you see it as
a destructive thought, yet you still can't escape it. The odds of you smoking a cigarette are not 0. Now the mind is clever, it could not just smoke
a cigarette and kill your mother, thats ridiculous. What happens is the pull of that entity, conditions the next thought ever so slightly,
slowly this takes form as my mother is pretty old, is she happy? Am i really never going to smoke ever again, what about my happiness, wouldn't she
want whats best for me, i'm suffering here. Basically the moral of the story is that the resolution of the conflict itself is what causes the conflict
to appear tomorrow. If smoking the cigarette didnt help you feel good, you wouldnt do it. Therefore, because it feels good you want to do it.
Yet you dont see that because it feels good, it creates the bad feeling that it then becomes necessary to neutralise. imagine you are neutral mostly.
then you smoke a cigarette you become good briefly, then you are plunged into bad because it wears off. so now you have gone from neutral, peace,
to good briefly, mostly bad. Now being mostly bad, you cant wait to feel good, so feeling bad you get the thought of a cigarette, now you have the
opportunity to feel good, you remember how it feels, you fixate on the experience, the coolness of the smoke. Now the moment feels tense, you feel bad
there is an option to make you feel good, yet you know that you are just giong to feel bad again after its done, yet reamining in the bad feels impossible.0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-col flex-1 mx-auto w-full max-w-[640px] px-8 py-8","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"mb-8 text-sm","children":["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/","className":"text-zinc-500 hover:text-zinc-300 transition-colors","children":"← Feed"}]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold mb-6","children":"Day 4"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-300 whitespace-pre-wrap","children":[["$","p","0",{"children":"dependent arising is a process that only happens now."}],["$","p","1",{"children":"e.g. ill have a cigarette today and start properly meditating tomorrow, is the same as i feel the urge to have a cigarette so im going to have one\nthe only difference is the story we generate to justify it"}],["$","p","2",{"children":"what happens every time is:"}],["$","p","3",{"children":"Delightful thought appears, a cigarette great idea!"}],["$","p","4",{"children":"The urge to fulfill the activity arises, ooh i want to do it now"}],["$","p","5",{"children":"This feels like a burning or friction in the body / mind, because now we have this moment and we have the desire for it to be different"}],["$","p","6",{"children":"This creates a tension, you sat there wanting a cigarette but not having one"}],["$","p","7",{"children":"This friction is actually elongated by the fixation of attention on the cigarette, the resistance to wanting a cigarette perpetuates the original\ndesire and adds to the pain felt in the moment. Any management techniques applied also keep the desired activity at the centre, its the same process\nwith more steps."}],["$","p","8",{"children":"So now there are 2 options. 1 - you resolve this internal conflict and pain and stress you are feeling by smoking a cigarette,"}],["$","p","9",{"children":"when you smoke this cigarette its a huge relief, not only because of the cigarette but you have now resolved the internal conflict!"}],["$","p","10",{"children":"What a relief! You notice how good it feels and then maybe carry on with what you were doing before, mood elevated, cigarettes are good for me."}],["$","p","11",{"children":"the next time u get the delightful thought to smoke a cigarette. That thought itself is birthed from the previous delight, the experience of the\ndropping of internal conflict even for a second. It feels like the ritual itself has become a semi-autonomous entity. Its as if this entity sends\nyou the delightful thought, you then carry the action out and strengthen the power of the entity, next time you do the action even quicker."}],["$","p","12",{"children":"$3"}],"$L4","$L5","$L6","$L7","$L8","$L9","$La","$Lb","$Lc","$Ld","$Le","$Lf","$L10","$L11","$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16","$L17","$L18","$L19","$L1a","$L1b","$L1c","$L1d","$L1e","$L1f","$L20","$L21","$L22","$L23","$L24","$L25","$L26","$L27","$L28","$L29","$L2a","$L2b","$L2c"]}]]}],null,"$L2d"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"F7DQ0WOyMnCYE5Tvy4WKI"}
4:["$","p","13",{"children":"So whats the solution?"}]
5:["$","p","14",{"children":"The solution is to see that this process is now happening by itself and you are caught in it unwillingly."}]
6:["$","p","15",{"children":"The second is seeing that you dont actually want the thing that is being delighted in, I dont want a cigarette, I want the relief and the ritual."}]
7:["$","p","16",{"children":"As a result, how can i get that same thing, that same relief in a slightly less harmful way?"}]
8:["$","p","17",{"children":"E.g. instead of smoking a cigarette, i sit outside with a coffee. This removes the fixation of the cigarette and gives evidence I just actually\nwanted a break, maybe some dopamine."}]
9:["$","p","18",{"children":"Then gradually continue this, coffee becomes just sitting outside, sitting outside becomes taking a few deep breaths, which then becomes staying with\nthe actual urge itself, seeing how it arises based on the promise of previous relief and how that is felt as more desireable or urgent based on how\nbad you are feeling now. Thus, the main solution is to feel good now. If you always felt happy why would you demand a cigarette, you wouldnt, you may\nstill like one but your happiness isnt dependent on having it."}]
a:["$","p","19",{"children":"This gradually weakens the momentum of the looped process / entity until there is no more delightful thought for a cigarette, partly because it is now\nnot delightful because you are already delighted with right now and because you have seen through the illusion that it was the cigarette doing this\nby replacing it with substituetes, until the mind doesn't know what it wants, it just wants NOT THIS or something to be different. This movement\nof wanting something to be different is becoming. Its the present moment transforming into a different view. This is usually habitual and feels forced\ne.g. the cigarette. Whats actually going on here is that the same experience is being created because it offers relief, it creates a world and sense of self\na storyline, identity. Thus, you never really quit cigarettes you just stop being the person that wants one."}]
b:["$","p","20",{"children":"The final truth is that you need to end the process of being reborn as a smoker, then you will never smoke again."}]
c:["$","p","21",{"children":"Buddhism takes this one step further and says once you end the process of being reborn as a 'me' you will never feel this stress again, because it is\nthe end of wanting this moment to be different than it currently is. There is no more delightful thought that drives activity that pushes and pulls\nto create certain experiences again and again, the whole structure has lost momentum."}]
d:["$","p","22",{"children":"love the idea of giving the chain form, its like we break it down into its different parts using nanananda, then we create a form that we can use to from a relationship with it, then we skillfully negotiate what is actually wanted. we swap cigarette with coffee, gradually we come to see that this is just a habitual movement occuring by itself to no-one, seeing this, the movement is allowed to stop, yet this only stops with the stopping of the self, becaue that IS what causes the movement"}]
e:["$","p","23",{"children":"need becoming to make this moment ok. dammn thats deep, thats the very self structure isnt it, even if im becoming bad or good, its this craving that fuels rebirth, its an addiction to becoming, because if im not a good or bad self then who am i, what is the world? how to make sense of current reality"}]
f:["$","p","24",{"children":"yes and even in like reactions to conflict. if something is not my fault, i default to taking blame because this action is what the archetype of the nice person would do, its the same becoming of the role, the whole thing is just becoming of actions that reinforce archetypes that help manage reality. i need to see myself as a good person thus i act in a certain way, me being a good person gives me an anchor and can help me judge if another person is or not, yet im not a good person im fueling my image of myself as a good person by taking actions in accordance with it thus i then becoming better at playing a good person, continually trying to become one but never do, because there is no such thing as a good and bad person"}]
10:["$","p","25",{"children":"Becoming = the movement by which experience organizes itself into \"I am this kind of one, in this kind of world, needing this kind of outcome.\""}]
11:["$","p","26",{"children":"Becoming is the performative crystallization of craving into identity."}]
12:["$","p","27",{"children":"Or more plainly:"}]
13:["$","p","28",{"children":"Becoming is what happens when the mind tries to solve discomfort by becoming someone in relation to it."}]
14:["$","p","29",{"children":"what else is along this chain? its like theres a link connecting nanananda, lacan, bourdrillard, terrence mckenna that gives different levels of the same thing. the vortex spins, how and why this happens relationally realting to emotions and social needs, then how these are influenced by cultural expectations and programming. how else could we add to this. its like culture is its own uncosncious with its own traumas, archetypes, a mind of its own right which places individuals into context and contains certain attractors for what status means, which characters may be played which then affects the development of the people within them because each person is being affected by these held norms and it affections action like a matric through this same process of becoming, its like a macro charged thoughtform that each person is feeding through their image of what it is. people in england do this, i am a person in england, i do this"}]
15:["$","p","30",{"children":"A sign becomes charged.\nThe charge creates desire.\nDesire seeks recognition/relief.\nA role is born.\nThe role creates a world.\nAction feeds the world and strenghtens the role.\nThe world feels real.\nThe self is continually reborn inside it, usually in a similar way because we have found one that meets our needs"}]
16:["$","p","31",{"children":"this stuff is blowing my mind. at the core of it is the mental process of dependent origination and craving, its just this same thing across scale, scaled up to mind its like self organising cells that group together to form actions taht defend against certain situations, which gets charged and reinforced by actions that solidify taht identity, then u look for proof this identity is real by performing it in the world, finding people who validate it, associating in environments where the perfromance is accepted and recognised by culture"}]
17:["$","p","32",{"children":"Yes. You've got it."}]
18:["$","p","33",{"children":"At the core is dependent arising as a self-organising process:"}]
19:["$","p","34",{"children":"feeling → craving → grasping → becoming → birth of a self/world"}]
1a:["$","p","35",{"children":"And then this scales."}]
1b:["$","p","36",{"children":"Nibbāna is not biologically reducible to a brain-state."}]
1c:["$","p","37",{"children":"But a biologically grounded description could be:"}]
1d:["$","p","38",{"children":"the deconditioning of compulsive self-modeling around affective regulation."}]
1e:["$","p","39",{"children":"Or more plainly:"}]
1f:["$","p","40",{"children":"the organism still responds to conditions, but affective pressure no longer crystallizes into \"me and my becoming.\""}]
20:["$","p","41",{"children":"Here is the full chain:"}]
21:["$","p","42",{"children":"Perception/interface:\nA world appears already structured by biology, culture, memory, and past action."}]
22:["$","p","43",{"children":"Contact:\nSomething is encountered."}]
23:["$","p","44",{"children":"Feeling:\nIt is marked pleasant/unpleasant/neutral."}]
24:["$","p","45",{"children":"Craving:\nThe organism wants more, less, or different."}]
25:["$","p","46",{"children":"Intention/kamma:\nA direction of action forms."}]
26:["$","p","47",{"children":"Action:\nBody, speech, or mind moves."}]
27:["$","p","48",{"children":"Result:\nRelief, pain, reward, shame, recognition, etc."}]
28:["$","p","49",{"children":"Update:\nThe interface is modified."}]
29:["$","p","50",{"children":"Future perception:\nThe sign appears with more or less charge."}]
2a:["$","p","51",{"children":"Becoming:\nA self is more or less likely to be born around it."}]
2b:["$","p","52",{"children":"Final formulation"}]
2c:["$","p","53",{"children":"Kamma is the feedback law of becoming."}]
2d:["$","$L2e",null,{"children":["$","$2f",null,{"name":"Next.MetadataOutlet","children":"$@30"}]}]
